<C>__{barbara}
<D>__{you risk alienating your cabinet and your party.}
<C>__{mandela}
<D>__{your advice is duly noted, barbara.}
<C>__{barbara}
<D>__{madiba ... the people want this. they hate the springboks. they don't want to be represented by a team they cheered against all their lives.}
<C>__{mandela}
<D>__{yes, i know. but in this instance the people are wrong. and it is my job as their elected leader to make them see that.}
<A>__{mandela leans forward to talk to linga.}
<C>__{mandela}
<D>__{can you tell the boys that madiba wants to go to eersterust, very fast.}
<A>__{linga murmurs into his radio. the convoy pulls out, very fast. barbara makes one last plea.}
<C>__{barbara}
<D>__{you're risking your political capital. you're risking your future as our leader.}
<C>__{mandela}
<D>__{the day i am afraid to do that is the day i am no longer fit to lead.}
